###############################################################################
# OBJECTIVE
###############################################################################
Conduct comprehensive audit of current design implementation:
- Document all glass/glow usage across screens
- Identify design inconsistencies
- Catalog CSS custom properties and their usage
- List all animation effects currently in use
- Map login screen design elements to be propagated

###############################################################################
# SCOPE
###############################################################################
Files to audit:
  - src/index.css (design tokens)
  - src/styles/app-bg.css (background animations)
  - src/components/screens/*.tsx (all 8 screens)
  - src/components/ui/*.tsx (UI components)
  - src/components/*.tsx (app-level components: Logo, AppBg, MobileHeader, ThemeToggle)

###############################################################################
# DELIVERABLES
###############################################################################
output:totem/instances/navitrack/sprints/44/S44-AUDIT.md

Document must include:
1. Current Design Elements Analysis
   - Glass effects inventory (.glass, .glass-input, .glass-glow, .glass-strong)
   - Animation inventory (glass-input-pulse, rainbow-glow-pulse, app-bg-pulse)
   - Color palette (primary, destructive, muted, etc.)
   - Typography tokens
   - Spacing/sizing tokens

2. Screen-by-Screen Analysis
   For each of 8 screens:
   - Glass/glow usage (which classes, where)
   - Inconsistencies vs login screen
   - Missing design elements
   - Custom/ad-hoc styles that should use tokens

3. Component Analysis
   - Existing UI components using glass effects
   - Components that need glass variants
   - Opportunities for new reusable components

4. Performance & Accessibility Notes
   - Current animation performance concerns
   - Missing prefers-reduced-motion support
   - Color contrast issues (if any)
   - Missing ARIA labels

5. Recommendations
   - Priority list for design system extraction
   - Suggested new components
   - Refactoring opportunities

###############################################################################
# ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
###############################################################################
verify:
  - [ ] S44-AUDIT.md exists in sprint folder
  - [ ] All 8 screens documented
  - [ ] All CSS custom properties catalogued
  - [ ] Inconsistencies clearly identified
  - [ ] Recommendations actionable for T2-DesignSystem

